Afeez Hanafi A non-governmental organisation, Bountiis Charity with a focus on Muslim women says it has empowered over 40 females through a workshop on exportation businesses. A statement on Saturday said the programme, tagged, ‘Mini-Exportation Workshop,’ held in Lagos recently to support budding entrepreneurs and create an alternative revenue generation for women. The Chairperson, Bountiis Board of Trustees, Dr Falilat Jimoh, in her welcome address stated that the group aspired to empower Muslim women to become enlightened and thrive as individuals and members of the Muslim community, adding that the workshop would contribute to the economic development of the country. Copyright PUNCH.
